th a chair.";i:36;s:75:"A leg crossover is a great way to learn to dance with props such as chairs.";i:37;s:97:"Stand next to a chair and cross one leg in front of the other keeping your ankles close together.";i:38;s:64:"Bend forward at your hips and rest your palms on the chair seat.";i:39;s:48:"Make sure that your legs and back stay straight.";i:40;s:29:"Bend down like a sex goddess.";i:41;s:75:"Slowly unwrap your legs from the chair and stand between their spread legs.";i:42;s:171:"Place your hands on their knees and move toward their face and then slowly lower yourself until youre moving your body from side to side with your face near their stomach.";i:43;s:67:"Recover means put the weight back on the foot that stayed in place.";i:44;s:27:"ROCKING CHAIR 4 count move.";i:45;s:40:"One foot stays in place The other moves.";i:46;s:85:"Rock forward on foot 1 step foot 2 in place rock back on foot 1 step foot 2 in place.";i:47;s:22:"Some start back first.";i:48;s:20:"1 Rock forward on R.";i:49;s:65:"Chair is used as a prop as prison bars shackles a safe haven etc.";i:50;s:121:"Lighting defines the space that the dancers perform in and gives the impression of a confined space LIGHTING Description.";i:51;s:68:"Mostly white lighting used focused on centre stage around the chair.";i:52;s:67:"When the prisoner performs his solos a single white shaft of light.";i:53;s:93:"Make sure you dance the hora before your chair lifters and the crowd gets too drunk or rowdy.";i:54;s:59:"We recommend dancing as soon as you can after the ceremony.";i:55;s:99:"A good time might be after cocktail hour or directly after the FatherDaughter and MotherSon dances.";i:56;s:74:"Pick your chair-lifters ahead of time and teach them how to lift properly.";i:57;s:283:"Classification in para dance sport To ensure competition is fair and equal all Para sports including Para dance sport have a system in place which ensures that winning is determined by skill fitness power endurance tactical ability and mental focus the same factors that account for.";i:58;s:138:"La Vibora de la Mar meaning sea snake is a song that wedding guests sing and dance to holding hands in a circle around the married couple.";i:59;s:136:"Eventually the dancers will duck under a bridge formed by the bride and groom holding hands and standing on chairs in facing each other.";i:60;s:106:"Another traditional Jewish wedding dance is the Krenzl and is performed when the last daughter is married.";i:61;s:100:"The mother of the bride is seated on a chair in the center of a circle formed by family and friends.";i:62;s:94:"She is then crowned with flowers while her daughters and other female guests dance around her.";}}